Bits and Pieces:

Endemic: A disease that is always present in an area. Think malaria in the tropics.

Epidemic: A sudden rise in cases of a disease. Think HIV/AIDS in the 1980s.

Pandemic: An epidemic that has spread far and wide. Think Covid-19 presently. https://t.co/LDSdFqagWD
